Operatives of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) on Friday arrested 12 suspected internet fraudsters in an early morning swoop on a club in Ikoyi, Lagos. Also seized during the raid were 10 exotic cars abandoned by their fleeing owners. “Operatives of the EFCC early this morning raided Club 57 in Ikoyi, Lagos, acting on intelligence report of activities of suspected Internet fraudsters,” the Commission said in a tweet. “While some abandoned their exotic cars to evade arrest, some others resisted. 12 suspects were arrested with 10 cars recovered.” 